tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE PrintingParameters (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_name STRING,
    print_quality STRING,
    paper_type STRING,
    ink_level FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE printing_parameters (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_id INT,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(50),
    parameter_value VARCHAR(50),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE quality_assurance (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    printer_id INT,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(50),
    passed BOOLEAN,
    checked_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE PrintingLogs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  printer_model_id INT NOT NULL,
  printing_parameter_id INT NOT NULL,
  success BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE PrintingParameters (
    parameter_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(255),
    parameter_type VARCHAR(50),
    machine_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (machine_id) REFERENCES PrintingMachine(machine_id)
);

CREATE TABLE QualityChecks (
    check_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    parameter_id INT,
    check_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    result VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (parameter_id) REFERENCES PrintingParameters(parameter_id)
);

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceLogs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    machine_id INT,
    log_description TEXT,
    log_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (machine_id) REFERENCES PrintingMachine(machine_id)
);
